<subSubSection id="C368652E93558E08F2AAF90AFAF4F91C" pageId="12" pageNumber="496" type="description">
<paragraph id="8BCD36A593558E08F2AAF90AFAF4F91C" blockId="12.[151,1437,1688,2039]" pageId="12" pageNumber="496">
<materialsCitation id="3B1A3CF893558E08F2AAF90AFAF0F91C" ID-GBIF-Occurrence="3798147317" collectorName="J. Serrano" pageId="12" pageNumber="496" specimenCount="2" typeStatus="lectotype">
The specimen here designated as 
<typeStatus id="54C9880793558E08F034F90AFDA1F979" box="[521,624,1688,1714]" pageId="12" pageNumber="496">lectotype</typeStatus>
is a male bearing labels “ 
<taxonomicName id="4C724D2693558E08F1B7F90AFC35F979" authorityName="Dejean" authorityYear="1829" box="[906,996,1688,1714]" class="Insecta" family="Carabidae" genus="Harpalus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="12" pageNumber="496" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="pallidus">
<emphasis id="B906EAB793558E08F1B7F90AFC35F979" box="[906,996,1688,1714]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="496">pallidus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
m. in Hispania”, “ex-Museo Chaudoir” and “ 
<typeStatus id="54C9880793558E08F2EDF92FFE97F91C" box="[208,326,1725,1751]" pageId="12" pageNumber="496">Lectotype</typeStatus>
, and a red card stating 
<taxonomicName id="4C724D2693558E08F07AF92EFBFFF91C" authority="Dejean, 1829" authorityName="Dejean" authorityYear="1829" box="[583,1070,1724,1751]" class="Insecta" family="Carabidae" genus="Harpalus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="12" pageNumber="496" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="pallidus" subGenus="Ophonus">
<emphasis id="B906EAB793558E08F07AF92EFC40F91D" box="[583,913,1724,1750]" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="496">Harpalus (Ophonus) pallidus</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation id="EFE34B5493558E08F1A5F92EFBFFF91C" author="Dejean, P. F. M. A." box="[920,1070,1724,1751]" pageId="12" pageNumber="496" refId="ref10732" refString="Dejean, P. F. M. A. (1829) Species general des coleopteres de la collection de M. le Comte Dejean. Tome quatrieme. Mequignon- Marvis, Paris, vii + 520 pp." type="book" year="1829">Dejean, 1829</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
desig. by 
<collectorName id="2687537393558E08F69CF92FFAC6F91C" box="[1185,1303,1725,1751]" pageId="12" pageNumber="496">J. Serrano</collectorName>
”
</materialsCitation>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="C368652E93558E08F2FAF972FAF0F83C" pageId="12" pageNumber="496" type="description">
<paragraph id="8BCD36A593558E08F2FAF972FE1BF864" blockId="12.[151,1437,1688,2039]" pageId="12" pageNumber="496">
<bibRefCitation id="EFE34B5493558E08F2FAF972FEB6F930" author="Dejean, P. F. M. A." box="[199,359,1760,1787]" pageId="12" pageNumber="496" refId="ref10732" refString="Dejean, P. F. M. A. (1829) Species general des coleopteres de la collection de M. le Comte Dejean. Tome quatrieme. Mequignon- Marvis, Paris, vii + 520 pp." type="book" year="1829">Dejean (1829)</bibRefCitation>
stated in the description that: 
<emphasis id="B906EAB793558E08F089F973FD85F8D5" italics="true" pageId="12" pageNumber="496">
Je possède trois individus de cette espèce: j’ai trouvé les deux premiers en 
<collectingCountry id="F365763593558E08F2C6F897FE8FF8D5" box="[251,350,1797,1822]" name="Spain" pageId="12" pageNumber="496">Espagne</collectingCountry>
, près de Palencia....
</emphasis>
The 
<typeStatus id="54C9880793558E08F0B7F896FD20F8D5" box="[650,753,1796,1822]" pageId="12" pageNumber="496">lectotype</typeStatus>
shows a cordiform pronotum with side notably sinuate before the posterior angle, which is well-marked and protruding backward. The elytra show a dark spot well-marked, that is paler in the female from the same locality (
<typeStatus id="54C9880793558E08F0B6F8DEFCF8F8AC" box="[651,809,1868,1895]" pageId="12" pageNumber="496">paralectotype</typeStatus>
). Likewise, it also shows strong punctures in the prosternum, a diagnostic character not mentioned by Dejean. For keys to identify the species see 
<bibRefCitation id="EFE34B5493558E08F6A7F8E3FAEAF840" author="Fuente de la, J. M." box="[1178,1339,1905,1931]" pageId="12" pageNumber="496" refId="ref10490" refString="Fuente de la, J. M. (1927) Tablas analiticas para la clasificacion de los coleopteros de la Peninsula Iberica. Adephaga: I Cicindelidae, II Carabidae. J. Bosch, Barcelona, 415 pp." type="book" year="1927">Fuente (1927)</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation id="EFE34B5493558E08F775F8E2FF33F864" author="Jeannel, R." pageId="12" pageNumber="496" pagination="572 - 1173" refId="ref11231" refString="Jeannel, R. (1942) Coleopteres carabiques. Deuxieme partie. Faune de France 40. Librairie de la Faculte des Sciences, Paris, pp. 572 - 1173." type="book chapter" year="1942">Jeannel (1942)</bibRefCitation>
and 
<bibRefCitation id="EFE34B5493558E08F32AF806FE14F864" author="Antoine, M." box="[279,453,1940,1967]" pageId="12" pageNumber="496" pagination="315 - 465" refId="ref10238" refString="Antoine, M. (1959) Coleopteres Carabiques du Maroc. Troisieme partie. Memoires de la Societe des Sciences Naturelles et Physiques du Maroc, Nouvelle Serie, Zoologie, 6, 315 - 465." type="journal article" year="1959">Antoine (1959)</bibRefCitation>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BCD36A593558E08F2FAF82BFAF0F83C" blockId="12.[151,1437,1688,2039]" pageId="12" pageNumber="496">
Its distribution is somewhat disjunct, as it is recorded from the western Mediterranean (the record from 
<collectingCountry id="F365763593558E08F751F82BFF04F83C" name="Morocco" pageId="12" pageNumber="496">Morocco</collectingCountry>
needs corroboration), 
<collectingCountry id="F365763593558E08F3ECF84EFDF9F83D" box="[465,552,2012,2038]" name="Algeria" pageId="12" pageNumber="496">Algeria</collectingCountry>
, the Levant, 
<collectingCountry id="F365763593558E08F08AF84EFCC8F83D" box="[695,793,2012,2038]" name="Armenia" pageId="12" pageNumber="496">Armenia</collectingCountry>
and southern 
<collectingCountry id="F365763593558E08F18BF84EFBD0F83D" box="[950,1025,2012,2038]" name="Russia" pageId="12" pageNumber="496">Russia</collectingCountry>
(
<bibRefCitation id="EFE34B5493558E08F62DF84FFAC4F83C" author="Jaeger, B. &amp; Kataev, B. M." box="[1040,1301,2013,2039]" pageId="12" pageNumber="496" pagination="1837" refId="ref10991" refString="Jaeger, B. &amp; Kataev, B. M. (2017) Subtribe Stenolophina Kirby, 1837. In: Lobl, I. &amp; Lobl, D. (Eds.), Catalogue of Palaearctic Coleoptera. Vol. 1. Revised and Updated Edition. Brill, Leiden, pp. 562 - 577." type="book chapter" year="2017">Jaeger &amp; Kataev, 2017</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
